content: That's really helpful, thank you! I think I'll try some poke and loco moco during my trip, and maybe stop by Mama's Fish House or The Fish Hopper for dinner. By the way, I'm staying at a luxurious resort in Maui that costs over $300 per night, so I'm trying to balance out the cost by looking for free or affordable activities and dining options. Do you have any recommendations for some affordable breakfast or brunch spots in Maui?
